ts": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Definitely don\u2019t start your Final Fantasy VII experience with Rebirth", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of Cloud Strife in Final Fantasy VII Rebirth.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BAggG_DfypU5Bm9HtrjbpSCfWf8=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73173815/EN_25_ff7rebirth_SS_0207_Trailer.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Square Enix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"lQUzFB\"><em>Final Fantasy VII Rebirth</em> is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24079544/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-review-ps5\">an excellent game</a> and an important evolution for the franchise. It mashes together a traditional RPG with a large open world, managing to feel both modern and like it\u2019s sticking to its 32-bit roots. What it is not, however, is a good place to get started with the multipart story that is <em>Final Fantasy VII</em> \u2014 despite what its creators might say.</p>\n<p id=\"CwzPS8\">Prior to <em>Rebirth</em>\u2019s launch, creative director and <a href=\"https://hard-drive.net/hd/video-games/square-enix-reveals-final-fantasy-fa", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/29/24085625/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-best-start", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T18:52:28+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Sony\u2019s new \u2018slim\u2019 PlayStation 5 is already on sale with Marvel\u2019s Spider-Man 2", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The PlayStation 5 slim sitting on a white surface with a blue backlight.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/z0OLnkU_BflbfRe8O3NceMBcJxo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73173791/110923_new_Playstation_5_Slim_ADiBenedetto_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Sony\u2019s latest console is still a big boi, even if it is more than 30 percent smaller.</em> | Photo by Antonio G. Di Benedetto / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Ba3w8s\">PlayStation 5 sales have <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/12/20/24009270/playstation-5-sales-surpass-50-million-units-sony\">already surpassed 50 million units</a> \u2014 a solid figure for a console that has rarely received a substantial price drop since it arrived on the scene more than three years ago. If you have yet to pick up Sony\u2019s latest console, however, <a href=\"https://howl.me/clJHf7mO8MP\">Best Buy is now offering</a> the new PS5 \u201cslim\u201d with a digital copy of <a href=\"h", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/29/24086116/playstation-ps5-slim-keychron-c3-pro-mechanical-keyboard-anker-qi2-charger-deal-sale", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T18:11:22+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Final Fantasy VII Rebirth: all the news and updates", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Final Fantasy VII: Rebirth featuring the iconic villain Sephiroth wreathed in flames with his back to the viewer.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cB-_Nz34RbzBynekvq5FNmzTI9c=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73156490/EN_06_FF7REBIRTH_Demo.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Square Enix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p>In Rebirth, our heroes get to explore beyond the confines of Midgar.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24078609/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-news-updates-trailers\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24078609/final-fantasy-7-rebirth-news-updates-trailers", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T18:08:08+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Final Fantasy VII Rebirth\u2019s creators want you to embrace the stress", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot from Final Fantasy VII Rebirth featuring a close up of Cloud (left) and Sephiroth (right) clashing swords.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3ZByfyK2ng_sr5ZbQw0oKkOvDv0=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73173592/EN_01_ff7rebirth_SS_0207_Trailer.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Square Enix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Don\u2019t worry, there\u2019ll be plenty of \u2018wonder and excitement\u2019 to embrace as well.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/29/24086758/final-fantasy-vii-rebirth-interview-naoki-hamaguchi-yoshinori-kitase\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/29/24086758/final-fantasy-vii-rebirth-interview-naoki-hamaguchi-yoshinori-kitase", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T18:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Microsoft updates Windows 11 with improved Copilot, Widgets, and more", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Windows 11 running on a tablet\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Km0W-tbg_XijqQBxQ7OweY1h-xk=/0x0:1650x1100/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73173516/windows11main.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Microsoft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"U12CVV\">Microsoft is starting to roll out a new update to Windows 11 that includes a whole host of improvements and new built-in features. Copilot in Windows 11 is getting more options to control your PC as part of this update, alongside a new Generative Erase option in Photos, Voice Shortcuts for accessibility, improved Snap layouts, changes to the Widgets system, and more.</p>\n<p id=\"ef5w0B\">While the Windows 11 update is available starting today, Microsoft says not all features will be enabled straight away. Copilot\u2019s new options will start rolling out in late March, enabling new skills like being able to ask the AI chatbot to enable the battery saver mode or to laun", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/29/24085496/microsoft-windows-11-update-copilot-widgets-snap-layouts-features", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T17:49:08+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Passing the Kids Online Safety Act just got more complicated", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage showing a child attempting to use a tablet screen that has a combination lock.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/YlTYSwjum6UyiJohUUUol4Wntu0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73173480/STK461_INTERNET_CHILD_SAFETY_Stock_D_CVirginia.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Jf254H\">Just a couple of weeks after the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/15/24073878/kids-online-safety-act-new-senate-support\">Kids Online Safety Act (KOSA) surged with enough support to position it to clear the Senate</a>, the path to new child protections on the internet suddenly looks more complex. Seeing the momentum, other lawmakers and outside groups sense it might be time to promote their own favored solutions, which could snarl KOSA\u2019s Senate passage.</p>\n<p id=\"1qvV2J\">Sen. Brian Schatz (D-HI), for example, sees this as an opportune moment for his own <a href=\"https://www.sc", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/29/24086559/kids-online-safety-act-schatz-tech-groups", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T16:30:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "The golden age of DVDs isn\u2019t over yet for anime fans", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage featuring screenshots from two animes licensed through Discotek.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/nyGkBDGTmRrIII7IoJu7EhvaNko=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73173202/236948_PHYSICAL_MEDIA_DISCOTEK_CVIRGINIA_copy.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Collage by Cath Virginia / The Verge | Images courtesy of Discotek</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Physical media might seem like it\u2019s on its deathbed, but the anime DVD and Blu-ray industry couldn\u2019t be more alive.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24062618/anime-dvd-bluray-discotek-physical-media\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24062618/anime-dvd-bluray-discotek-physical-media", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T16:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "As Gaza is bombarded, GoFundMe donations are stuck in limbo", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage illustrating the difficulties experienced by people fundraising for Palestinians.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5KGhl-hte9GhyGByjd_Z1XrFmjE=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73173046/247028_Gaza_Donation_Sanction_CVirginia_B.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos from Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p class=\"p--has-dropcap p-large-text\" id=\"KqI5PV\">By the end of January, more than 25,000 Palestinians had been reported killed as a result of Israel\u2019s military assault on Gaza. Just a handful of doctors remained at the largest medical facility in the Gaza Strip, where <a href=\"https://www.cnn.com/2024/01/08/middleeast/gaza-children-losing-legs-disease-intl-hnk/index.html\">every day, 10 children lost one or both of their legs</a> amid the Israeli military\u2019s siege. A weeklong communications blackout \u2014 <a href=\"https://www.cnn.com/2024/01/18/middleeast/gaza-communic", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/29/24085175/gofundme-gaza-palestine-fundraiser-under-review-esims", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T16:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "El Ni\u00f1o expected to smash heat records in 2024", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"El Nino Phenomenon Causes Drought In Tangerang\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_2o89NG0M94t4-uje2gHScJ84dQ=/0x0:4122x2748/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73173050/1730853179.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>A man squats on cracked, dry ground. Dead, dry fish lay on the ground where a pond used to be. | Photo by Kevin Herbian/NurPhoto via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"VSwzRa\">There\u2019s a 90 percent chance that global average surface temperatures will reach a record high for the year leading up to June 2024, according to new <a href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-024-52846-2\">research</a> published today in the journal <em>Scientific Reports</em>. Some places will be more sweltering than others, particularly in parts of Asia. The heat has cascading effects, like raising the risk of drought and wildfire. </p>\n<p id=\"yqsztu\">A weather pattern known as El Ni\u00f1o is to blame. El Ni\u00f1o is part of a natural, cycl", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/29/24085921/el-nino-forecast-record-heat-2024", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T15:33:27+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Apple\u2019s self-repair program now includes M3-powered Macs", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The M3 Max MacBook 16 in space black in front of a teal and white background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/zYqRmymTPl-D4wzR51O5usmSCJ8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73172951/236896_MacBook_Pro_16_M3_AKrales_0617.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"MFEmlP\"><a href=\"https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2024/02/apple-expands-self-service-repair-for-mac/\">Apple has expanded</a> its Self Service Repair program to include the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23949207/apple-macbook-pro-16-m3-max-review-price-specs\">MacBook Pro</a> and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23951082/apple-imac-m3-review-24-inch\">iMac</a> models powered by its M3 processor. That means users with the company\u2019s latest Mac hardware can now access the tools, parts, and repair manuals they need to fix their devices from <a href=\"https://selfservicerepair.com/en-US/home\">Ap", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/29/24086560/apple-self-repair-m3-macbook-imac", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T15:30:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "How to modernize your retro game collection in a few convoluted steps", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/zQWD95a0zkKREbyKGoiXN2YCUbs=/0x0:2700x1800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73172940/246964_PHYS_digital_games_made_phys_AKrales_0026.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>All you need are NFC stickers, a reader, a MiSTer, and a lot of patience to add a physical touch to ROMs.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24072166/retro-classic-game-roms-nfc-mister-how-to-modern\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "