_id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Crypto firm Gemini to pay over $1 billion back to customers in settlement", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of a digital coin on fire.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/it6Mk5YqpLEvjQMW8gtW3Ruerww=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73172791/acastro_220524_STK428_0003.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"8Jwtzp\">The cryptocurrency exchange Gemini has <a href=\"https://www.dfs.ny.gov/reports_and_publications/press_releases/pr202402282\">promised to return $1.1 billion</a> to customers as part of <a href=\"https://www.dfs.ny.gov/system/files/documents/2024/02/ea20240228_co_geminitrustcompanyllc.pdf\">a settlement it reached</a> with New York\u2019s Department of Financial Services (NYDFS). Gemini will also have to pay $37 million to the NYDFS \u201cfor significant failures that threatened the safety and soundness of the company.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"ISL1ba\">The NYDFS claims Gemini, which is owned by twins Tyler and Cameron Winklevoss, had \u201ccompliance, management, an", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/29/24086501/crypto-firm-gemini-ny-regulator-settlement", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T14:30:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Subscription services are changing our relationship to gaming", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage illustrating the inaccessibility of game libraries because of the switch to streaming.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Y_pJaTjzgW0GzCtNXitEiQt4NkU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73172771/236948_PHYSICAL_MEDIA_GAMEPASS_CVIRGINIA.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos by Vjeran Pavic and Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>In countries like Argentina, where physical games are exorbitantly expensive, services like Game Pass present a more affordable \u2014 but flawed \u2014 alternative.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24044155/xbox-game-pass-subscription-preservation-argentina\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24044155/xbox-game-pass-subscription-preservation-argentina", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T14:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "TinyLetter, in memoriam", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of a white dove carrying the TinyLetter logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/olpcDDFtmFQRvZ6O-5EmTAMz7d4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73172657/247034_Death_of_TinyLetter_STILL_CVirginia_A.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos from Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>In remembrance of the humblest newsletter service and its brief run nurturing great personal writing on the internet.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24085737/tinyletter-mailchimp-shut-down-email-newsletters\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24085737/tinyletter-mailchimp-shut-down-email-newsletters", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T13:43:52+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "Biden administration is investigating security threats from Chinese vehicles", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The interior of a BYD Tang all Electric EV car is displayed during the Geneva Motor Show 2024 at Palexpo on February 26, 2024\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/JWzVArBD4fmFZKboKbP6TTiGL0g=/6x0:6042x4024/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73172625/2043952282.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Policymakers are concerned that Chinese vehicle companies like BYD could collect sensitive data from drivers in the US.</em> | Photo by John Keeble / Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"hzduzN\">The US government is opening an investigation into the potential risks to national security posed by smart car technology produced in China and \u201cother countries of concern.\u201d </p>\n<p id=\"gELVBH\">The US Commerce Department\u2019s probe will focus on \u201cconnected vehicles\u201d \u2014 a broad term that can be applied to any car with internet access \u2014 amid concerns that technology like cameras, sensors, and on-board computers could be exploited to collect sensi", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/29/24086490/us-biden-administration-investigation-chinese-vehicles-security-threat", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T13:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "pag