ft_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"k8zYnB\">Microsoft has outlined a new Windows API designed to offer a seamless way for game developers to integrate super resolution AI-upscaling features from Nvidia, AMD, and Intel. In a new <a href=\"https://devblogs.microsoft.com/directx/directx-innovation-on-display-at-gdc-2024/\">blog post</a>, program manager Joshua Tucker describes Microsoft\u2019s new DirectSR API as the \u201cmissing link\u201d between games and super resolution technologies, and says it should provide \u201ca smoother, more efficient experience that scales across hardware.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"yS4q9Y\">\u201cThis API enables multi-vendor SR [super resolution] through a common set of inputs and outpu", "page_rating": 0, "bookmarked": false, "album": "", "user": null, "artist": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/29/24086443/microsoft-directsr-super-resolution-api", "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "thumbnail": null, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0}, {"tags": [], "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-02-29T11:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "source_obj__id": 359, "language": "en", "page_rating_contents": 0, "comments": [], "age": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "title": "This \u2018Amazon\u2019s Choice\u2019 video doorbell could let just about anyone spy on you", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4b7YmdXiSr7G6cC1dfU6XEfgiN0=/0x0:2467x1645/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73172319/aiwit_video_doorbell.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>An \u201cAiwit\u201d doorbell camera. There are many like it.</em> | Image via Amazon</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Iv8afw\">Does your video doorbell look anything like the one in the picture? Perhaps you bought it for cheap at Amazon, Temu, Shein, Sears, or Walmart? Does it use <a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/aiwit/id148458